  "text": "Conventional diagnostic imaging methods cannot accurately distinguish NASH from simple steatosis, nor can they assess the severity of fibrosis. However, transient elastography by FibroScan (Echosens, France) has been recently demonstrated to be an accurate and reproducible technique to identify children and adolescents with significant degrees of liver fibrosis [CITATION_1] .",
